[=]VERSE SERVE[=]ref In the beginning God created the heavens and the earth. - Genesis 1:1 WEB
[=]VERSE SERVE[=]ref Now the earth was formless and empty. Darkness was on the surface of the deep. God`s Spirit was hovering over the surface of the waters. - Genesis 1:2 WEB
[=]VERSE SERVE[=]ref God said, "Let there be light," and there was light. - Genesis 1:3 WEB
[=]VERSE SERVE[=]ref God saw the light, and saw that it was good. God divided the light from the darkness. - Genesis 1:4 WEB
[=]VERSE SERVE[=]ref God called the light Day, and the darkness he called Night. There was evening and there was morning, one day. - Genesis 1:5 WEB
[=]VERSE SERVE[=]ref God said, "Let there be an expanse in the midst of the waters, and let it divide the waters from the waters." - Genesis 1:6 WEB
[=]VERSE SERVE[=]ref God made the expanse, and divided the waters which were under the expanse from the waters which were above the expanse, and it was so. - Genesis 1:7 WEB
[=]VERSE SERVE[=]ref God called the expanse sky. There was evening and there was morning, a second day. - Genesis 1:8 WEB
[=]VERSE SERVE[=]ref God said, "Let the waters under the sky be gathered together to one place, and let the dry land appear," and it was so. - Genesis 1:9 WEB
[=]VERSE SERVE[=]ref God called the dry land Earth, and the gathering together of the waters he called Seas. God saw that it was good. - Genesis 1:10 WEB
[=]VERSE SERVE[=]ref God said, "Let the earth put forth grass, herbs yielding seed, and fruit trees bearing fruit after their kind, with its seed in it, on the earth," and it was so. - Genesis 1:11 WEB
[=]VERSE SERVE[=]ref The earth brought forth grass, herbs yielding seed after their kind, and trees bearing fruit, with its seed in it, after their kind: and God saw that it was good. - Genesis 1:12 WEB
[=]VERSE SERVE[=]ref There was evening and there was morning, a third day. - Genesis 1:13 WEB
[=]VERSE SERVE[=]ref God said, "Let there be lights in the expanse of sky to divide the day from the night; and let them be for signs, and for seasons, and for days and years; - Genesis 1:14 WEB
[=]VERSE SERVE[=]ref and let them be for lights in the expanse of sky to give light on the earth," and it was so. - Genesis 1:15 WEB
[=]VERSE SERVE[=]ref God made the two great lights: the greater light to rule the day, and the lesser light to rule the night. He also made the stars. - Genesis 1:16 WEB
[=]VERSE SERVE[=]ref God set them in the expanse of sky to give light to the earth, - Genesis 1:17 WEB
[=]VERSE SERVE[=]ref and to rule over the day and over the night, and to divide the light from the darkness. God saw that it was good. - Genesis 1:18 WEB
[=]VERSE SERVE[=]ref There was evening and there was morning, a fourth day. - Genesis 1:19 WEB
[=]VERSE SERVE[=]ref God said, "Let the waters swarm with swarms of living creatures, and let birds fly above the earth in the open expanse of sky." - Genesis 1:20 WEB
[=]VERSE SERVE[=]ref God created the large sea creatures, and every living creature that moves, with which the waters swarmed, after their kind, and every winged bird after its kind. God saw that it was good. - Genesis 1:21 WEB
[=]VERSE SERVE[=]ref God blessed them, saying, "Be fruitful, and multiply, and fill the waters in the seas, and let birds multiply on the earth." - Genesis 1:22 WEB
[=]VERSE SERVE[=]ref There was evening and there was morning, a fifth day. - Genesis 1:23 WEB
[=]VERSE SERVE[=]ref God said, "Let the earth bring forth living creatures after their kind, cattle, creeping things, and animals of the earth after their kind," and it was so. - Genesis 1:24 WEB
[=]VERSE SERVE[=]ref God made the animals of the earth after their kind, and the cattle after their kind, and everything that creeps on the ground after its kind. God saw that it was good. - Genesis 1:25 WEB
[=]VERSE SERVE[=]ref God said, "Let us make man in our image, after our likeness: and let them have dominion over the fish of the sea, and over the birds of the sky, and over the cattle, and over all the earth, and over every creeping thing that creeps on the earth." - Genesis 1:26 WEB
[=]VERSE SERVE[=]ref God created man in his own image. In God`s image he created him; male and female he created them. - Genesis 1:27 WEB
[=]VERSE SERVE[=]ref God blessed them. God said to them, "Be fruitful, and multiply, and replenish the earth, and subdue it. Have dominion over the fish of the sea, and over the birds of the sky, and over every living thing that moves on the earth." - Genesis 1:28 WEB
[=]VERSE SERVE[=]ref God said, "Behold, I have given you every herb yielding seed, which is on the surface of all the earth, and every tree, which bears fruit yielding seed. It will be your food. - Genesis 1:29 WEB
[=]VERSE SERVE[=]ref To every animal of the earth, and to every bird of the sky, and to everything that creeps on the earth, in which there is life, I have given every green herb for food." And it was so. - Genesis 1:30 WEB
[=]VERSE SERVE[=]ref God saw everything that he had made, and, behold, it was very good. There was evening and there was morning, the sixth day. - Genesis 1:31 WEB
